<number box="[870,898,1752,1776]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="13.0">13</number>
A, 
<number box="[939,968,1752,1776]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="13.0">13</number>
F). Style well developed, articulated to connective well below aedeagal atrium, in lateral view with apodeme and apophysis both nearly straight with junction forming obtuse angle; apodeme long, spatulate; apophysis slightly longer than apodeme, apex weakly or not expanded, with preapical tooth or angle (
<figureCitation box="[698,790,1860,1885]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1574,1596]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,205,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[177,1409,193,1552]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. The holotype of Decliviassus bipunctatus sp. nov. A. Genital capsule, lateral view; B. Aedeagus, lateral view; C. Style, lateral view; D. Subgenital plates, ventral view; E. Ventral process of pygofer side, caudolateral view; F. Apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253719/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
Figs 
<number box="[761,790,1860,1884]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="10.0">10</number>
