D, 
<number box="[963,992,1860,1884]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" value="13.0">13</number>
C). Aedeagus simple, tubular basally, compressed distally, U-shaped in lateral view, preatrium absent, atrium in posterior view without well developed ventrolateral lobes, dorsal apodeme columnlike; shaft with pair of slender processes distad of gonopore extended basolaterad, apex tapered in lateral and posterior views; gonopore preapical on posterior surface with inner surface glabrous (
<figureCitation box="[262,348,2004,2029]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="16.[151,250,1574,1596]" captionTargetBox="[190,1399,205,1542]" captionTargetId="figure@16.[177,1409,193,1552]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="FIGURE 10. The holotype of Decliviassus bipunctatus sp. nov. A. Genital capsule, lateral view; B. Aedeagus, lateral view; C. Style, lateral view; D. Subgenital plates, ventral view; E. Ventral process of pygofer side, caudolateral view; F. Apex of aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/253719/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
